      <memberdef kind="function" id="class_mux_controller_1a05848de25ac2dbec233935058a1d24b4" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int init</definition>
        <argsstring>()</argsstring>
        <name>init</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>The MUX Controller init function. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="return"><para>Returns 0 in case of success, error code ENODEV otherwise</para>
</simplesect>
The function enters a loop over the array of muxer select lines and checks if the GPIO at index i is ready for usage with call of function device_is_ready. If a GPIO is not ready, the function returns immediately with error code ENODEV. Afterwards it checks if the muxer is enabled and the enable GPIO is not ready for usage. In this case the function returns with error code ENODEV, otherwise enable GPIO is set to inactive and functions returns 0. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
